readingKunHtml: いかん, なに, なんぞ
sourceMeaningMnemonic:
You're holding a <radical>sword</radical> in front of <radical>two</radical> <radical>building</radical>s. <kanji>What</kanji> will you do?

A. Stab the building on the left.

B. Stab the building on the right.

What do you choose?
meaningInfo: What? Do you think I'm gonna help you make this decision? No way, you need to dig deep and think about what you want to do.
readingMnemonic:
A. <kanji>What</kanji> is, stab the building on the left? You stab the building on the left with your sword and what comes out is... a plate of delicious <reading>na</reading>chos (<ja>な</ja>)!

B. <kanji>What</kanji> is, stab the building on the right? You stab the building on the right with your sword and what comes out is... a plate of delicious <reading>na</reading>chos (<ja>な</ja>)!
readingInfo: What?! You got nachos either way. You should be happy, don't ask me any other questions.
